  "description": "In the daemon start handler (handle_daemon for DaemonCommand::Start), after spawning the daemon run subprocess, wait 3-5 seconds and verify the process is still alive. If it died immediately, read the log file (from TASK logging) and return the error to the user. Currently spawn_autonomous_daemon_run returns Ok(pid) even if the subprocess crashes 1ms later, giving the user a false 'daemon started' message. Also add this check to the MCP ao.daemon.start tool response.",
